1 (3) Money Except as otherwise provided in this section, money
2 in the fund at the close of the fiscal year shall remain remains in
3 the fund and shall does not lapse to the general fund.
4 (4) The department is the administrator of the fund for audits
5 of the fund.
6 (5) Money in the fund may be expended, upon on appropriation,
7 as follows:
8 (a) Not more than $1,700,000.00 annually may be expended for
9 the administrative costs of the department and the board in
10 implementing this part and part 361.
11 (b) After expenditures for the administrative costs under
12 subdivision (a), money in the fund may be expended, upon on
13 approval of the board, to provide grants to local units of
14 government pursuant to under section 36203.
15 (c) If, after expenditures under subdivisions (a) and (b), the
16 amount of money remaining in the fund exceeds $5,000,000.00, money
17 in the fund may be expended, upon on approval of the board,
18 pursuant to under part 361 for the purchase of development rights
19 to farmland or the acquisition of agricultural conservation
20 easements.
21 (6) Expenditures of money in the fund as provided in this part
22 are consistent with the state's interest in preserving farmland and
23 are for an important public purpose.
24 (7) For the fiscal year ending September 30, 2027,
25 $2,000,000.00 must be transferred from the fund to the state
26 general fund.
27 (8) For the fiscal year ending September 30, 2028,
28 $2,000,000.00 must be transferred from the fund to the state
